contentrichtext.text: {{tocright}} '''Yellow Submarine''' may refer to: ==The Beatles== *[[Yellow Submarine (song)|"Yellow Submarine" (song)]], released in 1966 *[[Yellow Submarine (film)|''Yellow Submarine'' (film)]], a feature-length animated film featuring The Beatles' music *[[Yellow Submarine (album)|''Yellow Submarine'' (album)]], 1969 soundtrack to the film *''[[Yellow Submarine Songtrack]]'', 1999 expanded remix of the ''Yellow Submarine'' album *[[Yellow Submarine (sculpture)|''Yellow Submarine'' (sculpture)]], large-scale work of art at Liverpool Airport, based on the song and film *''[[Ringo's Yellow Submarine]]'', 1983 radio show hosted by Ringo Starr * ''The Yellow Submarine'', 1968 movie comic book published by [[Gold Key Comics]]. ==Submarines== * ''Yellow Submarine'', nickname for an unmanned acoustic test vehicle, originally the American submarine [[USS Menhaden (SS-377)|USS ''Menhaden'' (SS-377)]] * ''Yellow Submarine'', nickname for ''[[Quester I]]'', built in an attempt to salvage the wreck of the SS ''Andrea Doria'' ==Sports== *"The Yellow Submarine", nickname for the Spanish football team [[CÃ¡diz CF]] *"The Yellow Submarines", nickname for the Spanish football team [[Villarreal CF]] {{disambig}}
